  "prompt": "How does Airbnb prevent users from contacting hosts outside of the site?",
  "response": "Airbnb has several mechanisms to discourage and prevent users from communicating outside their platform:\n\n1. Message monitoring\n- All communication between guests and hosts must occur through Airbnb's messaging system\n- Messages are automatically scanned for contact information attempts\n\n2. Communication blocking\n- The platform blocks phone numbers, email addresses, and other direct contact details\n- Attempts to share external contact information are automatically filtered\n\n3. Penalties for platform violation\n- Users who attempt to communicate outside the platform can be warned or banned\n- Hosts and guests risk losing their ability to book or host\n\n4. User interface design\n- The messaging system is integrated directly into the booking process\n- External communication is discouraged through user experience design\n\n5. Terms of service\n- Users agree to communicate exclusively through Airbnb's platform\n- Violations can result in account suspension\n\nThese measures help Airbnb maintain transaction security, protect user privacy, and ensure they can mediate any potential disputes or issues between guests and hosts.",
